  "text": "The reliability of the HOS-Brazil was investigated using a sample of 70 patients who responded to the questionnaire twice with a 48-h interval. In between applications, no new medications, therapies, or procedures were introduced that were likely to induce rapid changes to the patients' clinical conditions. The interval between the test and retest was selected based on two criteria: The period of time was held long enough for the respondents not to remember their previous responses but was simultaneously brief enough for no changes to occur to the patients' clinical conditions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
